--- PART 4: HIGHER ENERGY INVARIANTS ---
E_2 = sum r(n)^2 (standard additive energy)
E_3 = sum r(n)^3 (cubic energy)
E_4 = sum r(n)^4 (quartic energy)
Question: do (E_2, E_3) determine H better?

  p=7:
    Distinct (E2,E3) pairs: 2
    (E2=15, E3=27): H=[189], count=2
    (E2=19, E3=45): H=[175], count=6
    H determined by (E2, E3)? True

  p=11:
    Distinct (E2,E3) pairs: 4
    (E2=65, E3=175): H=[95095], count=2
    (E2=69, E3=205): H=[92411], count=10
    (E2=73, E3=235): H=[93467], count=10
    (E2=85, E3=325): H=[93027], count=10
    H determined by (E2, E3)? True

  p=13:
    Distinct (E2,E3) pairs: 6
    (E2=114, E3=378): H=[3703011], count=4
    (E2=118, E3=408): H=[3704857], count=12
    (E2=118, E3=420): H=[3683797], count=12
    (E2=122, E3=450): H=[3669497], count=12
    (E2=130, E3=522): H=[3707483], count=12
    (E2=146, E3=666): H=[3711175], count=12
    H determined by (E2, E3)? True

