--- PART 7: WHY E anti-correlates with H at p=3 mod 4 ---
At p=7 (3 mod 4): max E = Interval, but max H = Paley
At p=13 (1 mod 4): max E = Interval = max H

Insight: Walsh degree-2 contribution f_2(sigma) depends on
the Legendre character chi at p=3 mod 4, creating sign reversal.
At p=1 mod 4, chi(-1)=+1 so no reversal; degree-4 takes over.

  p=7 (3 mod 4): chi(-1) = -1
    At p=3 mod 4: chi(-1)=-1, Paley tournament exists
    At p=1 mod 4: chi(-1)=+1, NO Paley tournament
    The sign reversal in Walsh degree-2 is controlled by chi(-1)

  p=11 (3 mod 4): chi(-1) = -1
    At p=3 mod 4: chi(-1)=-1, Paley tournament exists
    At p=1 mod 4: chi(-1)=+1, NO Paley tournament
    The sign reversal in Walsh degree-2 is controlled by chi(-1)

  p=13 (1 mod 4): chi(-1) = 1
    At p=3 mod 4: chi(-1)=-1, Paley tournament exists
    At p=1 mod 4: chi(-1)=+1, NO Paley tournament
    The sign reversal in Walsh degree-2 is controlled by chi(-1)
